import pandas as pd

from matplotlib.ticker import FuncFormatter

Introduction¶

Data¶

The data comes from here. It is 12 months of historical bike share data (January 2021 - December 2021).

Goal¶

Convert casual riders to annual members in order to increase revenue.

Task¶

Find the answer to the following: How do annual members differ from casual riders?

Data Import and Clean-up¶

Adding Features¶

In [ ]:
df['ride_length'] = df['ended_at'] - df['started_at']
df['day_of_week'] = df['started_at'].dt.day_name() #day_name() for name, dt.dayofweek for number
df['day_num'] = df['started_at'].dt.dayofweek + 1
days = ['Monday', 'Tuesday', 'Wednesday',
        'Thursday', 'Friday', 'Saturday',
        'Sunday']

df['month'] = df['started_at'].dt.month
months = ['Jan', 'Feb', 'Mar', 'Apr',
          'May', 'Jun', 'Jul', 'Aug',
          'Sep', 'Oct', 'Nov', 'Dec']

df['quarters'] = np.ceil(df['month'] / 3).astype(int)

df['start_hour'] = df['started_at'].dt.hour
df['ride_length_s'] = df['ride_length'].dt.total_seconds()
df['ride_length_m'] = round(df['ride_length_s']/60, 2)
In [ ]:
member = df[df['member_casual'] == 'member']
casual = df[df['member_casual'] == 'casual']
In [ ]:
trips_df = pd.DataFrame()

trips_df['total_trips'] = [df.shape[0]]
trips_df['total_trips_member'] = [member.shape[0]]
trips_df['total_trips_casual'] = [casual.shape[0]]
trips_df['member_pct'] = round((trips_df['total_trips_member'] / trips_df['total_trips']) * 100, 2)
trips_df['casual_pct'] = round((trips_df['total_trips_casual'] / trips_df['total_trips']) * 100, 2)
In [ ]:
top_start_stations = df['start_station_name'].value_counts().head(10).index
top_start_stations = sorted(top_start_stations, key=lambda x: df['start_station_name'].value_counts()[x])
top_end_stations = df['end_station_name'].value_counts().head(10).index
top_end_stations = sorted(top_end_stations, key=lambda x: df['end_station_name'].value_counts()[x])
top_stations = df[df['start_station_name'].isin(top_start_stations) & df['end_station_name'].isin(top_end_stations)]

filtered_members = df.dropna(subset=['start_station_name', 'end_station_name']).loc[df['member_casual'] == 'member']
top_start_stations_members = filtered_members['start_station_name'].value_counts().head(10)
top_end_stations_members = filtered_members['end_station_name'].value_counts().head(10)
top_stations_members = pd.concat([top_start_stations_members, top_end_stations_members], axis=1, keys=['Start', 'End']).reset_index()
top_stations_members = top_stations_members.melt(id_vars='index', var_name='Type', value_name='Number of Rides')

filtered_casual = df.dropna(subset=['start_station_name', 'end_station_name']).loc[df['member_casual'] == 'casual']
top_start_stations_casual = filtered_casual['start_station_name'].value_counts().head(10)
top_end_stations_casual = filtered_casual['end_station_name'].value_counts().head(10)
top_stations_casual = pd.concat([top_start_stations_casual, top_end_stations_casual], axis=1, keys=['Start', 'End']).reset_index()
top_stations_casual = top_stations_casual.melt(id_vars='index', var_name='Type', value_name='Number of Rides')

Conclusion¶

Key Points¶

Members¶
  • Trips made: 55.4% of 2021 trips
  • Favorite Station: Clark St & Elm St
  • Peak Time: 17:00
  • Rush Hour: Morning and Evening
  • Peak Season: Summer
  • Low Season: Winter
  • Ride Length: Stable throughout the year
Casual Riders¶
  • Trips made: 44.6% of 2021 trips
  • Favorite Station: Streeter Dr & Grand Ave
  • Peak Time: 17:00
  • Rush Hour: Evening
  • Peak Season: Summer
  • Low Season: Winter (more drastic downturn than members)
  • Ride Length: Peaks during weekends
  • Casual riders out-ride members during the peak season

Recommendation¶

  1. Tap into different types of riders

Commuter Membership (targets existing members and potential members)

  • Priority usage morning and evening rush hour.

Recreational Membership (targets current casual riders)

  • Priority usage during weekends.
  • Introduce special rates or promotions for weekend rides.
  • Allow users to bring friends on rides at reduced rates (since use is mostly recreational, it could be likely that users typically ride with others)
  1. Tap into seasonality in ridership
  • Introduce incentives (ex. discounted membership) for users who sign up to be members during the low season.
